main event: A civilian reported observing a star-shaped object moving very fast low on the horizon in Monroe, New York on November 3, 1966.
interesting points: The object was noted to have green and red colors,The sighting lasted for about 2 minutes,The object moved from 120 degrees to the south at a high rate of speed,The witness claimed familiarity with UFOs but could not definitively classify this sighting,Investigative officers concluded it could possibly be an aircraft due to lack of supporting evidence.
witness description: Civilian couple, age 24, employed at Ford Motor Company
